    {
      "id": 358267,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Identify the different types of protons in the following molecule, and tell where you would expect each to absorb:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBalVVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--859e9e328f63dfda14cca96d24889b167acaba32/OChem_13_04_004.jpg\" alt=\"Two carbon atoms with a trans double bond in-between. C 1 is bonded to benzene with a methoxy group at C 4. C 2 is bonded to an ethyl group.\">",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "<p>There are seven kinds of protons labeled. The types and expected range of absorption of each follow. <b><i>a:</i></b> ether, 3.5–4.5 <i>δ</i>; <b><i>b:</i></b> aryl, 6.5–8.0 <i>δ</i>; <b><i>c:</i></b> aryl, 6.5–8.0; <b><i>d:</i></b> vinylic, 4.5–6.5 <i>δ</i>; <b><i>e:</i></b> vinylic, 4.5–6.5 <i>δ</i>; <b><i>f:</i></b> alkyl (secondary), 1.2–1.6 <i>δ</i>; <b><i>g:</i></b> alkyl (primary), 0.7–1.3 <i>δ</i>.</p>\n<img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBallVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--45e080bf13e0b945b7984642fba712ea81bcd8a5/OChem_13_EC_202.jpg\" alt=\"Structure of 1-[(E)-but-1-enyl]-4-methoxybenzene. Hydrogens labeled a (methoxy), b  and c (ortho and meta to methoxy), d (benzylic), e (trans to d), f (methylene), and g (methyl) .\">"
        }
      ],
      "community_solutions": []
    }
  ],
